    "title": {
      "rendered": "The Insights of 100,000 Nonprofit Technology Facebook Fans"
    },
    "content": {
      "rendered": "<p><a href=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/Nonprofit-Facebook-Insights.jpg\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-20024\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/Nonprofit-Facebook-Insights-300x300.jpg?resize=300%2C300\" alt=\"nonprofit-facebook-insights\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/Nonprofit-Facebook-Insights.jpg?resize=300%2C300&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/Nonprofit-Facebook-Insights.jpg?resize=150%2C150&amp;ssl=1 150w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/Nonprofit-Facebook-Insights.jpg?resize=200%2C200&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/Nonprofit-Facebook-Insights.jpg?resize=75%2C75&amp;ssl=1 75w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/Nonprofit-Facebook-Insights.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a>Last\u00a0week the <strong><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/nonprofitorgs\" target=\"_blank\">Nonprofit Tech for Good Facebook Page</a></strong> reached the 100,000 fans. It took 8 years, 4 months, and 22 days. Growth slowed significantly in February 2016\u00a0to approximately 200 new likes a month whereas in the year previous new likes averaged 800 per month. Overall, the page took 100 months to reach 100,000 likes, thus it has an average growth rate of 1,000 new likes a month. Does this mean anything? Not really, except that it confirms that recent algorithm changes have had a significant impact on both engagement and growth rates.</p>\n<h2>1. Despite a plummeting growth rate, referral traffic from Facebook to nptechforgood.com is still high.</h2>\n<p>With an average organic reach of 3%, it&#8217;s unlikely that the high referral traffic is coming directly from the Nonprofit Tech for Good Facebook Page, but rather from\u00a0nonprofit techies who are sharing Nonprofit Tech for Good blog posts on their pages and profiles. This is a bright spot for those of you discouraged by low organic reach.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/nonprofitorgs\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-20011\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/Referral-Traffic.png?resize=600%2C235\" alt=\"referral-traffic\" width=\"600\" height=\"235\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/Referral-Traffic.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/Referral-Traffic.png?resize=300%2C118&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">2. 53% of Nonprofit Tech for Good&#8217;s fans are female and the largest age group is 25-34 years old.</h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/nonprofitorgs\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-20012\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/Likes.png?resize=600%2C199\" alt=\"likes\" width=\"600\" height=\"199\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/Likes.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/Likes.png?resize=300%2C100&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">3. Females are responsible for 59% of the engagement that occurs on the Nonprofit Tech for Good Facebook Page.</h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/nonprofitorgs\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-20013\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/Engaged.png?resize=600%2C211\" alt=\"engaged\" width=\"600\" height=\"211\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/Engaged.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/Engaged.png?resize=300%2C106&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">4. The top three countries are the United States, India, and Pakistan. The top three cities are New York, Dhaka, and New Delhi.</h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/nonprofitorgs\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-20023\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/cities-1.png?resize=600%2C457\" alt=\"cities\" width=\"600\" height=\"457\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/cities-1.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/cities-1.png?resize=300%2C229&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">5. After much experimentation, Insights consistently reveal that photo posts get more engagement than links or videos.</h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/nonprofitorgs\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-20017\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/posts-1.png?resize=600%2C226\" alt=\"posts\" width=\"600\" height=\"226\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/posts-1.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/posts-1.png?resize=300%2C113&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">6. Only a tiny fraction of Nonprofit Tech for Good&#8217;s Fans click the call-to-action button \u2013 specifically .000003% on a good day.</h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/nonprofitorgs\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-20019\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/take-action-button.png?resize=600%2C242\" alt=\"take-action-button\" width=\"600\" height=\"242\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/take-action-button.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/take-action-button.png?resize=300%2C121&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">7. Nonprofit Tech for Good doesn&#8217;t get a whole lot of Love, or Wow, Haha, Sad, Angry, or Thankful.</h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/nonprofitorgs\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-20026\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/Love.png?resize=600%2C278\" alt=\"love\" width=\"600\" height=\"278\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/Love.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/Love.png?resize=300%2C139&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">8. The Facebook icon in the upper right of this blog\u00a0is the number one source of traffic to the Nonprofit Tech for Good Facebook Page outside of facebook.com.</h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/nonprofitorgs\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-20027\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/facebook-icon.png?resize=600%2C277\" alt=\"facebook-icon\" width=\"600\" height=\"277\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/facebook-icon.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/facebook-icon.png?resize=300%2C139&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<hr />\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 17px;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; font-weight: bold;\"><em>Mobile for Good: A How-To Fundraising Guide for Nonprofits</em></span></span></strong></h2>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Mobile-Good-How--Fundraising-Nonprofits/dp/0071825460\" target=\"_blank\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignleft wp-image-16024\" style=\"margin: 10px; border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/mobile-for-good-look-inside.jpg?resize=99%2C150\" alt=\"mobile for good look inside\" width=\"99\" height=\"150\" /></a>Based on more than 20 years of experience and 25,000+ hours spent utilizing mobile and social media, <a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Mobile-Good-How--Fundraising-Nonprofits/dp/0071825460\" target=\"_blank\"><em><strong>Mobile for Good: A How-To Fundraising Guide for Nonprofits</strong></em></a> is a comprehensive 256-page book packed with more than 500 best practices. Written on the premise that all communications and fundraising are now mobile and social, Mobile for Good is a step-by-step how-to guide for writing, implementing, and maintaining a mobile and social fundraising strategy for your nonprofit.</p>\n",
